# Portuguese and Play ‚Äî Story Generator

Generates bilingual (PT/EN) short stories for each chapter of the A1/A2 and B1
textbooks, cycling through 8 literary genres. Each story includes a full English
translation, a line-by-line interleaved version, grammar notes, and genre notes.

## Usage

```bash
python generate_stories.py                        # all chapters, both books
python generate_stories.py --book a1a2            # A1/A2 book only
python generate_stories.py --book b1              # B1 book only
python generate_stories.py --chapter A1-1         # single chapter
python generate_stories.py --dry-run              # print prompts, no API calls
python generate_stories.py --prompts-only         # save prompts as .txt, no API calls
python generate_stories.py --output ./my-stories  # custom output directory
python generate_stories.py --delay 3.0            # seconds between API calls (default: 2)
python generate_stories.py --chapter A1-1 --inspire "Ana finds a talking fish."
python generate_stories.py --chapter A1-1 --inspire-file seed.txt
```

Requires an `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` environment variable for live generation.

## Output

Stories are saved to `./stories/` (or `--output`) as markdown files with YAML
frontmatter. A `INDEX.md` index and (in `--prompts-only` mode) an `ALL_PROMPTS.md`
file are also written.

## Genres

Stories cycle through 8 genres in order: Absurdist Comedy, Rom-com, Magical
Realism, Noir / Crime Thriller, Telenovela Drama, Fairy Tale / F√°bula, Horror /
Suspense, Epistolary.

---

## Tests

Run the test suite with:

```bash
python3 -m pytest test_generate_stories.py -v
```

Tests also run automatically on every pull request via GitHub Actions.

### What is tested

#### `build_user_prompt` ‚Äî 12 tests
Verifies the prompt string sent to Claude is built correctly. Checks that the
chapter ID, title, book level, grammar points, objectives, genre name, and genre
description all appear in the output. Also tests the inspiration block: absent
when the argument is empty or whitespace-only, present and stripped when provided.

#### `generate_story` ‚Äî 14 tests
Covers the three execution paths:

- **`dry_run=True`** ‚Äî returns the raw prompt without calling the API and prints a
  `DRY RUN` header to stdout
- **`prompts_only=True`** ‚Äî same return value, no API call, no "Generating‚Ä¶" output
- **Live API path** ‚Äî confirms the Anthropic client is called with the right model,
  `max_tokens`, system prompt, and a correctly structured `messages` list; confirms
  the return value is `message.content[0].text`

Also checks that inspiration text flows through to the API payload in the live path.

#### `save_story` ‚Äî 18 tests
Checks files written to disk:

- **Markdown mode** ‚Äî correct filename and extension, frontmatter opens with `---`,
  all fields (`chapter`, `title`, `genre`, `grammar`, `objectives`) present,
  `grammar` and `objectives` are valid JSON, story content appears after frontmatter
- **Prompts-only mode** ‚Äî writes a `.txt` file containing the system prompt header,
  system prompt body, user prompt header, and content in that order
- **Filename sanitisation** ‚Äî slashes in chapter IDs and genre names (e.g.
  `"Noir / Crime Thriller"`) are replaced with dashes
- **Encoding** ‚Äî Portuguese characters survive a UTF-8 write/read roundtrip

#### `main` / CLI ‚Äî 30 tests
Integration-level tests that call `main()` with different `sys.argv` values:

- **Chapter counts** ‚Äî `--book a1a2`, `--book b1`, and `--book both` produce the
  right number of rows in `INDEX.md`; `--chapter` filters to exactly one
- **Invalid chapter** ‚Äî prints a "not found" message and exits before writing
  `INDEX.md`
- **Genre cycling** ‚Äî genres assigned in order, wrap back to `GENRES[0]` after all
  8 are used; a single filtered chapter always gets `GENRES[0]`
- **`--inspire` / `--inspire-file`** ‚Äî inspiration text passed through to
  `generate_story`; missing file prints a warning; using `--inspire` without
  `--chapter` prints a "best with --chapter" warning
- **Output directory** ‚Äî created automatically if it doesn't exist, including nested
  paths
- **`INDEX.md`** ‚Äî always created, correct header row, file links use `.md` normally
  and `.txt` in prompts-only mode
- **`ALL_PROMPTS.md`** ‚Äî created only in `--prompts-only` mode, contains the system
  prompt and a section per chapter; absent in dry-run and API modes
- **API mode** ‚Äî `anthropic.Anthropic()` called exactly once; story file created;
  `time.sleep` called between chapters (not after the last) and respects `--delay`
- **Error handling** ‚Äî an exception in one chapter is caught and the rest continue;
  error summary is printed
